    "explanation": "Diagram 1 provides a component-and-connector view with an emphasis on the interaction between the 'providers', 'usecases', and 'entities' layers. It visualizes the flow of data and control via connectors/arrows. Diagram 2 is more of a component-based declaration/description focusing on the components and grouping into different packages. It represents more of a package/class diagram rather than a runtime architecture diagram. Both diagrams share a similar high-level architectural structure (Providers, UseCases, and Entities) but diagram 1 provides more detail about runtime behavior with the connectors whereas diagram 2 provides more details on components with processors (AccountHolderProcessor, FinancialInstitutionProcessor, etc.). Diagram 1 also provides the interfaces that the components use to communicate. Finally, Diagram 2 includes components related to deployment/build (e.g., Main, Makefile, Modelbank Server) while Diagram 1 does not."
